 of your child.</p><p><strong>KidsCove (birth – Kindergarten)</strong> uses the <em>First Look </em>curriculum<em> </em>to give preschoolers a first impression of their loving heavenly Father. KidsCove keeps learning simple and fun, repeating one basic truth about God all month long. By the time a child graduates KidsCove, he/she should believe three key things: God made me, God loves me and Jesus wants to be my friend forever.</p><p><strong>KidsCreek (1<sup>st</sup> – 5<sup>th</sup> grade)</strong> is designed to take elementary-aged children on a fun, engaging journey of biblical learning. KidsCreek uses the <em>252 Basics</em> curriculum and incorporates live worship, large group teaching, drama and small groups. All components of KidsCreek teach children how to apply Biblical concepts and stories to everyday life.</p><p>Our children’s activities take place during our Sunday morning services. For more information, contact Leslie Ryser at <a href=\"mailto:leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com\">leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com</a> or 606.877.9682.</p><p><strong>What should I expect on my first visit?<br> </strong>Make your way to the Kids’ area and look for our check-in stations. We will ask you to provide some information about your family that we will use to place your child in our electronic check-in system. Once you are checked-in, one of our volunteers will show you to your child’s room.</p><p>You and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit. Your child will receive a name tag to wear, which includes a 4-digit number that matches the pick-up tag you receive. During check-out, you will return to your child’s room and show your pick-up tag in order for your child to be released back to you.</p><p><strong>What are your safety procedures?</strong><br> Security is a top priority for KidsCove and KidsCreek. All children are electronically checked-in, and foot traffic to children’s rooms is limited to ensure complete safety for all children. We also keep our child-to-volunteer ratio low in order to ensure the physical safety of each child. All volunteers working with children are required to complete a background check.</p><p><strong>What if my child needs me during the worship service?</strong><br> If you are needed during the worship service, the 4-digit code on your pick-up tag will appear on the screens in the auditorium. When you see your child’s code, immediately exit the auditorium and head to the KidsCove check-in desk. One of our team members will direct you to your child’s room.</p><p><strong>What should I expect as a regular attendee?</strong><br> Each week you will come to the kids check-in area, which opens 20 minutes before the start of each service. To check-in your child, use one of our touch screens to enter the last 7-digits of the phone number used to register your child.</p><p>You and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit. Your child will receive a name tag to wear, which includes a 4-digit number that matches your pick-up tag. During check-out, you will return to your child’s room and show your pick-up tag in order for your child to be released back to you.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 14:58:08','2015-05-19 19:50:33','532dfa4f-8f7a-4158-bd49-3aea97b4c5b2'),(77,80,'en_us','The-Creek-Easter-Weekend-0047',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 15:01:47','2015-05-19 15:01:47','2d329c57-4191-469c-9385-f903d4070d68'),(78,81,'en_us','The-Creek-Easter-Weekend-0047 1',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 15:21:18','2015-05-19 15:21:18','b4b3c539-9a7d-4d39-8328-b67ac6cf5f55'),(79,82,'en_us','The-Creek-Easter-Weekend-0047 2',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2015-05-19 16:12:07','2015-05-19 16:12:07','325b99d4-af84-4444-bd86-10f95d9a36b1'),(80,83,'en_us','The-Creek-Easter-Weekend-0047 3',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NUL