INSERT INTO `craft_entryversions` VALUES (1,2,1,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":\"1\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"The Creek Church\",\"slug\":\"homepage\",\"postDate\":1431370944,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>It\\u2019s true, this site doesn\\u2019t have a whole lot of content yet, but don\\u2019t worry. Our web developers have just installed the CMS, and they\\u2019re setting things up for the content editors this very moment. Soon Craft.dev will be an oasis of fresh perspectives, sharp analyses, and astute opinions that will keep you coming back again and again.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 14:35:48','2015-05-13 14:35:48','d0890e58-a417-4e77-91d5-4bb055c9ee5f'),(2,11,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"New Here?\",\"slug\":\"about\",\"postDate\":1431528827,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Welcome to Hawk Creek Church.<\\/p><p>It is our hope that you discover a warm, friendly group of people at \\u201cThe Creek.\\u201d Whether you\\u2019re single, married, with or without children \\u2013 no matter where you\\u2019ve been or what you\\u2019ve done \\u2013 you are welcome here.<\\/p><p>This section of our website will help you find out more about our story, beliefs, vision, and staff. Next Steps will help you discover how to move forward in your relationship with God. Children and Student ministries provide information on how we are reaching the next generation. Be sure to check out our messages at our Watch &amp; Listen section.<\\/p><p>Relax and enjoy your visit. We are glad you are here.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 14:53:47','2015-05-13 14:53:47','6f2102f1-b041-4543-a322-8e99e6c33d26'),(3,12,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Trevor Barton\",\"slug\":\"trevor-barton\",\"postDate\":1431529474,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>Trevor is the lead pastor of The Creek Church. A native of Middlesboro, Kentucky, Trevor came to The Creek in November of 2004. Under his leadership, the church has grown from a small, community fellowship into a thriving, outwardly focused instrument of change. Trevor is a gifted communicator and teacher, with a passion for presenting Biblical truth in a dynamic, relevant way. His passion is to lead people from all walks of life into an authentic, growing relationship with Jesus Christ. Trevor and his wife, Allison, have two sons, Shepherd and Greyson.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"trevor@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Lead Pastor\"}}','2015-05-13 15:04:34','2015-05-13 15:04:34','b493dcbb-071d-44a0-b690-17801d72490f'),(4,13,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Donna McClure\",\"slug\":\"donna-mcclure\",\"postDate\":1431529507,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>As Guest Services Director, Donna helps mobilize a team of weekly volunteers that seek to make first-time guests and regular attendees feel welcome from the moment they drive into the parking lot until after they head home.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"donna@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Guest Services Director\"}}','2015-05-13 15:05:07','2015-05-13 15:05:07','aeaad32d-8501-489c-9888-c6b60ab44102'),(5,14,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Debbie Gilbert\",\"slug\":\"debbie-gilbert\",\"postDate\":1431529537,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>Debbie came to Hawk Creek in March of 2006. Later that year she began fasting and praying, asking God to break her heart for what breaks His. She sensed God calling her into marriage and family ministries, and has been passionately pursuing that challenge ever since. Debbie holds a Bachelor\\u2019s Degree in Education from Berea College and a Master\\u2019s Degree in Marriage and Family Therapy from Liberty University. She counsels from a biblical worldview and believes God is the Healer of marriages and families. She and her husband, Doug, have one adult son named Kris.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"debbie@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Director of Celebrate Recovery & Pastoral Counseling\"}}','2015-05-13 15:05:37','2015-05-13 15:05:37','68e8a9e2-1100-44dd-8f58-ea020a8e52b2'),(6,15,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Leslie Ryser\",\"slug\":\"leslie-ryser\",\"postDate\":1431529563,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>Leslie has a passion for helping children and families become fully devoted followers of Christ. Before coming to The Creek, Leslie worked in Washington, DC, where she was part of a dynamic church body. She learned that biblical community doesn\\u2019t have to be boring \\u2013 it should be exciting, relevant and fun. She\\u2019s been sold out on serving Jesus ever since. As Kids\\u2019 Director, Leslie leads our KidsCove and KidsCreek environments. She also heads up our Love Loud projects. Leslie and her husband, Rocky, have a son named Ross.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"leslie@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Director of Children\\u2019s Ministries & Love Loud\"}}','2015-05-13 15:06:03','2015-05-13 15:06:03','a92b9ff8-789b-4de9-a731-70918c9e5271'),(7,16,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ryan Hartzell\",\"slug\":\"ryan-hartzell\",\"postDate\":1431529594,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>Ryan is the Student Pastor here at Hawk Creek. He has a passion for leading students to become fully devoted followers of Jesus Christ. A native of London, Ryan has been actively involved at The Creek since 2006, and has served in a variety of areas, including our worship, Somerset campus, and media ministries. Ryan holds a Bachelor\\u2019s Degree in Bible from Tennessee Temple University. He is an avid runner, reader and thinker.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"ryan@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Student Pastor\"}}','2015-05-13 15:06:34','2015-05-13 15:06:34','b890db4d-832d-41ba-bc49-7d725aa3ea39'),(8,17,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Shane McCowan\",\"slug\":\"shane-mccowan\",\"postDate\":1431529622,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>Shane has been involved with Christian music for more than a decade and serves as one of our Worship Leaders. He is an avid fan of all types of music and has a passion for using worship to draw people into a closer relationship with Christ. Shane and his wife Jessica are involved with our Fusion Student Ministry. They are the proud parents of two children, Haley and Dylan. In addition to serving at The Creek, Shane works as a Network Engineer for the Laurel County School System.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"shane@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Worship Leader\"}}','2015-05-13 15:07:02','2015-05-13 15:07:02','8dba5f93-cad7-4799-9bbe-ff708e687d58'),(9,17,5,1,'en_us',2,'','{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Shane McCowan\",\"slug\":\"shane-mccowan\",\"postDate\":1431529620,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>Shane has been involved with Christian music for more than a decade and serves as one of our Worship Leaders. He is an avid fan of all types of music and has a passion for using worship to draw people into a closer relationship with Christ. Shane and his wife Jessica are involved with our Fusion Student Ministry. They are the proud parents of two children, Haley and Dylan. In addition to serving at The Creek, Shane works as a Network Engineer for the Laurel County School System.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"\",\"7\":\"Worship Leader\"}}','2015-05-13 15:07:15','2015-05-13 15:07:15','c42b4e99-982b-4bb5-928f-b51c8195e756'),(10,18,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Austin Upchurch\",\"slug\":\"austin-upchurch\",\"postDate\":1431529667,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>As Creative Arts Pastor, Austin leads the Creative Arts Team to produce and deliver content that leads people to take a step closer to Jesus. Austin is passionate about developing visual media that provokes thought and ultimately, action. He is driven and inspired by Colossians 3:23: \\u201cI will pursue excellence in everything I do because I\\u2019m working for God, not man.\\u201d Austin is an avid fisherman and enjoys playing guitar. He and his wife, Jessie, enjoy watching movies, shopping, traveling and cooking together.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"austin@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Creative Arts Pastor\"}}','2015-05-13 15:07:47','2015-05-13 15:07:47','27995797-950f-4375-889e-04f22ce46372'),(11,19,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jonathan Bright\",\"slug\":\"jonathan-bright\",\"postDate\":1431529689,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>As Finance Pastor, Jonathan has oversight of the financials and accounting. He also serves as the Production Director, where he leads the Production Team for Sunday services and special events. Jonathan graduated from Cumberland College in 2004 with a double-major, earning Bachelor of Science degrees in Business Administration and Computer Information Systems. Jonathan and his wife Erica have three daughters, including a set of identical twins.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"jonathan@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 15:08:10','2015-05-13 15:08:10','fc944e21-69d4-4af6-9d17-61b6f30d0a0a'),(12,20,5,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jack Willis\",\"slug\":\"jack-willis\",\"postDate\":1431529722,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>Jack serves as our Next Steps Pastor and Administrator, guiding our new attendees to find their place at The Creek as well as overseeing day-to-day operations. A native of Corbin, Kentucky, Jack graduated from Cumberland College in 2001 with a Bachelor of Science degree, minor in Special Education. Jack is happily married to his wife, Suzanne. They have a son named Jackson and a daughter named Karis.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"jack@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Next Steps \\/ Administrator\"}}','2015-05-13 15:08:43','2015-05-13 15:08:43','8565161a-03b5-4163-8f6c-ffc9a68acf06'),(13,21,6,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"CVA Form\",\"slug\":\"cvas\",\"postDate\":1431531365,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"10\":\"http:\\/\\/www.bbcnews.com\"}}','2015-05-13 15:36:05','2015-05-13 15:36:05','f32e40a7-77ed-4542-8f32-486810c86102'),(14,22,6,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Last Year\'s CVA\",\"slug\":\"cvas-1\",\"postDate\":1431531463,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"10\":\"http:\\/\\/www.cnn.com\"}}','2015-05-13 15:37:43','2015-05-13 15:37:43','cd015893-0550-4d35-a5dc-f7d25d01c594'),(15,20,5,1,'en_us',2,'','{\"typeId\":\"5\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Jack Willis\",\"slug\":\"jack-willis\",\"postDate\":1431534600,\"expiryDate\":1431495000,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"9\":\"<p>Jack serves as our Next Steps Pastor and Administrator, guiding our new attendees to find their place at The Creek as well as overseeing day-to-day operations. A native of Corbin, Kentucky, Jack graduated from Cumberland College in 2001 with a Bachelor of Science degree, minor in Special Education. Jack is happily married to his wife, Suzanne. They have a son named Jackson and a daughter named Karis.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"jack@thecreekchurch.com\",\"7\":\"Next Steps \\/ Administrator\"}}','2015-05-13 16:08:44','2015-05-13 16:08:44','a07a5228-19cb-4c26-a66a-3a5694d582aa'),(16,23,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"About Us\",\"slug\":\"about-us\",\"postDate\":1431539947,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":\"\",\"13\":\"\\/about\"}}','2015-05-13 17:59:08','2015-05-13 17:59:08','39678488-ba2b-45b7-81cb-844bf11e8867'),(17,24,8,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":\"8\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Our Staff\",\"slug\":\"staffpage\",\"postDate\":1431540028,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Our staff is awesome!<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:04:41','2015-05-13 18:04:41','8c8dd3a7-866c-4531-aba7-bf4572038f62'),(18,25,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Staff\",\"slug\":\"staff\",\"postDate\":1431540322,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"24\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:05:22','2015-05-13 18:05:22','f1c763aa-f67a-4191-9f59-d3b9912201e7'),(19,26,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"What to Expect\",\"slug\":\"what-to-expect\",\"postDate\":1431540378,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>First, don\\u2019t stress over what to wear! We try to project a casual environment; on any typical Sunday, our pastor and worship teams will lead the way by sporting jeans and such. Feel free to dress comfortably and casually.<\\/p><p>From the moment you arrive on our campus, you will find a friendly, helpful atmosphere. Parking teams will assist you to our reserved parking area which exists for guests, seniors and those with special needs.<\\/p><p>Once inside, feel free to grab a cup of coffee or a light breakfast in our Creek Caf\\u00e9. Also, our Guest Services Center will be staffed by smiling volunteers ready and eager to answer any questions you might have. There you will also find various resources available for purchase that can help you in your journey of faith. In addition to books by leading authors, CDs and DVDs of our worship experiences are available.<\\/p><p>The doors to the auditorium, as well as the doors to KidsCreek and KidsCove, open 15 minutes before our 9:30 am and 11:15 am services. Prior to the auditorium doors opening, you will find ample space and lots of seating available in the caf\\u00e9 and foyer areas. Come early, hang out with your family or friends, and meet other Creekers.<\\/p><p>We have a first class facility ready to serve your children from birth through 5th grade. Our nursery is fully staffed by people who love kids. Our pre-school and children\\u2019s worship experience are also fully staffed by adults who want to love and lead your children to an incredible experience every single Sunday.<\\/p><p>Our worship experience is typically 70 minutes of dynamic, relevant high energy music, coupled with practical, yet theological teaching. We believe that the church is never supposed to be boring or predictable. Our goal is to provide a world-class worship experience every Sunday in order that Jesus may be made famous in our community and world.<\\/p><p>At the conclusion of each worship experience, you will be invited to a pastor\\u2019s reception area where you can meet our Lead Pastor and receive a special gift from The Creek just for being with us.<\\/p><p>We hope your experience at The Creek will be all you expected!<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:06:18','2015-05-13 18:06:18','1060ecda-ced4-490f-878b-8a5c472e2adb'),(20,27,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Our Story\",\"slug\":\"our-story\",\"postDate\":1431540403,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The Creek Church was founded in 1861 as Hawk Creek Baptist Church. For 144 years the church existed as a small community church, predominantly serving those living in and near the Hawk Creek area of Laurel County, Kentucky. In the early days, the average attendance ranged from 50 to 100 people.<\\/p><p>In 2005, God began a fresh move that brought revival and expanded the churches borders to reach throughout Laurel County, the region and into the world. Today, God is radically transforming and rebuilding lives at Hawk Creek. Since 2005, over 1000 people have been baptized and come to develop a personal relationship with Jesus Christ. Through the dynamic presentation of God\\u2019s unchanging word and the hands of His people, addictions have been shattered, broken marriages have been rebuilt and lives have been reborn.<\\/p><p>In February 2011, we moved into a new, state-of-the-art building located on a 40-acre campus in the London-Laurel County Industrial Park. The facility strategically positions us to make a bigger difference in our community and the world for generations to come.<\\/p><p>In March 2012, we launched a second campus in Somerset, Kentucky. We are now one church meeting in two locations. Our mission remains the same \\u2013 to love God and love people, and to lead those people to become fully devoted followers of Jesus Christ. Our vision for the future compels us to believe that the best days are still ahead!<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:06:43','2015-05-13 18:06:43','434d2939-74cd-4a00-8099-42ad32719b85'),(22,29,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Our Beliefs\",\"slug\":\"our-beliefs\",\"postDate\":1431540456,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>THE SCRIPTURES:<\\/strong> We believe that the entire Bible, all 66 books are inspired by God and inerrant in the original writings. Through the providence of God, the Word of God has been protected and preserved, and is the only infallible and authoritative rule of faith and practice. \\u2013 2 Timothy 3:16-17; 2 Peter 1:20-21; Psalm 119:11, 89, 105\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>GOD<\\/strong>: We believe there is only One true, eternally existent God. He exists in three co-equal persons \\u2013 Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. The triune God is the Creator and Sustainer of all things, and is worthy of worship and obedience. \\u2013 Deuteronomy. 6:4-5; Genesis 1:31, Luke 3:21-22; Matthew 28:18-20\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>JESUS CHRIST:<\\/strong> We believe that Jesus Christ is God. He was conceived by the Holy Spirit, born of a virgin, lived a sinless life, performed miracles, shed His blood on the cross to pay the debt for our sins, was buried, bodily resurrected, ascended to the right hand of the Father, and will return literally, visibly, and personally in glory and power. \\u2013 Matthew 1:18-23; Philippians 2:5-11; 1 Corinthians 15:1-8.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>HOLY SPIRIT:<\\/strong> We believe that the Holy Spirit is God, Co-equal and Co-existent with the Father and the Son. He is the Chief Convictor of sin and the Chief Agent of regeneration and sanctification. The Holy Spirit lives within every believer and empowers every believer to live a godly life. \\u2013 John 14:16-17; 16:7-15; 1 Corinthians 6:19-20; Romans 8:9-11.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>SALVATION:<\\/strong> We believe salvation is a free gift of God\\u2019s grace apart from human works, based solely upon Christ\\u2019s atoning death, received only through faith in the person and finished work of Jesus Christ on the cross and His resurrection from death. \\u2013 Ephesians 2:8-10; Acts 16:31.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>THE CHURCH:<\\/strong> We believe the church is the body of Christ and family of God. It is made up of saved and baptized believers, who regularly join together for worship, fellowship, and ministry. \\u2013 Matthew 16:15-19; I Corinthians 12:12-14; Hebrews 10:25.\\r\\n<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><strong>EVANGELISM:<\\/strong> We believe that it is the responsibility and privilege of every Christian to proclaim the good news of Jesus Christ and to seek to make growing disciples. \\u2013 Matthew 28:18-20; Acts 1:8.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:07:36','2015-05-13 18:07:36','9fb101c4-08f0-4152-ae4b-45ecc43bce4e'),(23,30,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"What to Expect\",\"slug\":\"what-to-expect\",\"postDate\":1431540479,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"26\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:07:59','2015-05-13 18:07:59','78927b66-0064-4441-8fb1-afcdc9156990'),(24,31,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Our Story\",\"slug\":\"our-story\",\"postDate\":1431540499,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"27\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:08:19','2015-05-13 18:08:19','4a842166-5198-4c81-b199-f3c5f95945c9'),(26,33,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Our Beliefs\",\"slug\":\"our-beliefs\",\"postDate\":1431540554,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"29\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:09:14','2015-05-13 18:09:14','1b6a4e78-5217-41b6-a322-36d1d2873915'),(27,34,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Services & Locations\",\"slug\":\"services-locations\",\"postDate\":1431540577,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<h2>Services &amp; Locations<\\/h2> <p><strong>London Weekly Activities<\\/strong><br> Weekend Services \\u2013 Sunday @ 9:30AM, 11:15AM<br> The Creek Kids \\u2013 Sunday @ 9:30AM, 11:15AM<br> Fusion Students \\u2013 Wednesday @ 6:30 PM<br> Celebrate Recovery \\u2013 Tuesday @ 6:00 PM<\\/p><p><strong>Location<\\/strong><br> The Creek Church<br> 75 Capital Drive<br> London, KY 40741<br> (Off Industrial Blvd \\/ Hwy 80 West)<br> See <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/hawkcreekchurch.com\\/maps\\\">Map &amp; Directions<\\/a><\\/p><p><strong>Somerset Weekly Activities<\\/strong><br> Weekend Services \\u2013 Sunday @ 10:00 AM<br> The Creek Kids \\u2013 Sunday @ 10:00 AM<br> Fusion Students \\u2013 Wednesday @ 6:30 PM<\\/p><p><strong>Location<\\/strong><br> The Center for Rural Development<br> 2292 South Highway 27<br> Somerset, KY 42501<br> See <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/hawkcreekchurch.com\\/somerset-map\\\">Map &amp; Directions<\\/a><\\/p><p><strong>Church Office &amp; Delivery Address<\\/strong><br> The Creek Church<br> 504 North Broad Street<br> London, KY 40741<br> Phone: 606.877.9682<br> Email: <a href=\\\"mailto:info@thecreekchurch.com\\\">info@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a><\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:09:37','2015-05-13 18:09:37','e8305d2a-f739-49b1-af93-83bba59936cf'),(28,35,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Services & Locations\",\"slug\":\"services-locations\",\"postDate\":1431540613,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"34\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:10:13','2015-05-13 18:10:13','a95cff58-6286-4d20-a0c9-cf255e311c82'),(29,36,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Next Steps\",\"slug\":\"next-steps\",\"postDate\":1431540785,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":\"\",\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:13:05','2015-05-13 18:13:05','617dd4f0-632c-43e2-bec1-b6a03803f06f'),(30,37,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Baptism\",\"slug\":\"baptism\",\"postDate\":1431540826,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Are you a follower of Jesus Christ? If so, have you gone public with your faith? At The Creek, we teach that every person who has accepted Christ should be baptized by water immersion. <strong>If you are a follower of Christ but have never been baptized by immersion, you are invited and encouraged to do so at our next Going Public service. <\\/strong>To be included in our next Going Public Service, contact:<\\/p><p><strong>London Campus \\u2013 Ron Green at <a href=\\\"mailto:ron@thecreekchurch.com\\\">ron@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682<br> Somerset Campus \\u2013 Rocky Ryser at <a href=\\\"mailto:rocky@thecreekchurch.com\\\">rocky@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.682.3625<\\/strong><\\/p><p>For more information on what we teach about baptism, check out some of the Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) below.<\\/p><p><strong>BAPTISM FAQ<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>1 \\u2013 WHY SHOULD I BE BAPTIZED?<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>To follow the example set by Christ.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cIn those days Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee and was baptized by John in the Jordan.\\u201d (Mark 1:9)<\\/p><p><strong>Because Christ commanded it.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cGo therefore and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, teaching them to observe all that I have commanded you. And behold, I am with you always, to the end of the age.\\u201d (Matthew 28:19-20)<\\/p><p><strong>It demonstrates that I am a Believer.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cAnd by this we know that we have come to know him, if we keep his commandments.\\u201d (1 John 2:3)<\\/p><p><strong>2 \\u2013 WHAT IS THE MEANING OF BAPTISM?<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>To illustrate Christ\\u2019s death, burial and resurrection.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cChrist died for our sins in accordance with the Scriptures, that he was buried, that he was raised on the third day in accordance with the Scriptures\\u201d (1 Corinthians 15:3-4)<\\/p><p>\\u201cHaving been buried with him in baptism, in which you were also raised with him through faith in the powerful working of God, who raised him from the dead.\\u201d (Colossians 2:12)<\\/p><p><strong>To illustrate my new life as a Christian.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cTherefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old has passed away; behold, the new has come.\\u201d (2 Corinthians 5:17)<\\/p><p>\\u201cWe were buried therefore with him by baptism into death, in order that, just as Christ was raised from the dead by the glory of the Father, we too might walk in newness of life.\\u201d (Romans 6:4)<\\/p><p><strong>3 \\u2013 IS BAPTISM NECESSARY FOR SALVATION?<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>No, baptism doesn\\u2019t make you a Christian.<br> <\\/strong>Only your faith in Christ makes you a Christian. Baptism is a public sign of the commitment you have made to follow Jesus Christ.<\\/p><p>\\u201cFor by grace you have been saved through faith. And this is not your own doing; it is the gift of God, not a result of works, so that no one may boast.\\u201d (Ephesians 2:8-9)<\\/p><p><strong>4 \\u2013 WHY BE BAPTIZED BY IMMERSION?<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>Because Jesus was baptized by immersion.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cAnd when Jesus was baptized, immediately he went up from the water\\u2026\\u201d (Matthew 3:16)<\\/p><p><strong>Every baptism in the Bible was by immersion.<br> <\\/strong>For example: \\u201cAnd he commanded the chariot to stop, and they both went down into the water, Philip and the eunuch, and he baptized him.\\u201d (Acts 8:38)<\\/p><p><strong>The word \\u201cbaptize\\u201d comes from the Greek word \\u201cbaptizo\\u201d which means \\u201cto dip\\u201d or \\u201cto immerse\\u201d under water.<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>It best symbolizes a burial and resurrection<br> <\\/strong>As a person being baptized goes under water, he\\/she is identifying with the death of and burial of Christ. As he\\/she comes up out of the water, he\\/she is identifying with the resurrection of Christ. (see Romans 6:1-11)<\\/p><p><strong> 5 \\u2013 WHO SHOULD BE BAPTIZED?<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>Every person who has believed in Jesus Christ.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cSo those who received his word were baptized, and there were added that day about three thousand souls.\\u201d (Acts 2:41)<\\/p><p>\\u201cBut when they believed Philip as he preached good news about the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.\\u201d (Acts 8:12)<br> <strong><br> The one requirement for baptism is belief in Christ.<br> <\\/strong>A Believer is someone who has realized that their sin separated them from God. They have given up all efforts to reach God through good works or religious activity. They have concluded that Jesus Christ\\u2019s death on the cross for their sins is the only thing that can bridge the gap between them and God. A Believer is someone who has decided to trust Christ alone for their salvation. If you have come to that point in your spiritual journey, then you are ready to be baptized.<\\/p><p><strong>6 \\u2013 WHEN SHOULD I BE BAPTIZED?<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>As soon as you believe.<br> <\\/strong>Acts 8:12 says: \\u201cBut when they believed Philip as he preached good news about the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.\\u201d<\\/p><p>This doesn\\u2019t have to be immediately but the Bible teaches that baptism should follow your decision to become a Believer. There is no reason to delay. If you wait until you are \\u201cgood\\u201d enough, you will never feel ready for baptism.<\\/p><p><strong>7 \\u2013 WHAT ABOUT BEING BAPTIZED TWICE?<br> <\\/strong>The Creek Church recommends being baptized again if you have not been baptized by immersion since you became a Believer in Christ. It does not devalue a prior experience but simply reflects your desire to be baptized in the same way Jesus was baptized.<\\/p><p><strong>8 \\u2013 WHAT DO I WEAR TO BE BAPTIZED?<br> <\\/strong>Dress in clothes you don\\u2019t mind getting wet. We will give you a dark shirt to wear and recommend shorts. Be sure to bring a change of dry clothes to wear home. There is a changing room available. We will provide you with a towel but recommend you also bring one from home. Arrive 30 minutes before the service is scheduled to begin for some final instructions.<\\/p><p><strong>9 \\u2013 HOW DO I SIGN UP TO BE BAPTIZED?<br> <\\/strong>You can sign up to be baptized by contacting Ron Green at <a href=\\\"mailto:ron@thecreekchurch.com\\\">ron@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:13:46','2015-05-13 18:13:46','07427519-eb0c-42bd-a478-4c6f384f44b7'),(31,38,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Membership\",\"slug\":\"membership\",\"postDate\":1431540847,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>There are three ways to become a member of The Creek Church:<\\/p><p><strong>Baptism:<\\/strong> This means you have received Jesus Christ as your savior and are ready to identify with Him publicly by being baptized by immersion in water.<\\/p> <p><strong>Transfer of a Letter of Membership:<\\/strong> This means you have received Jesus Christ as your savior, been baptized by immersion, and are a member of another Baptist church.<\\/p> <p><strong>Statement of Faith:<\\/strong> This means you have received Jesus Christ as your savior and been baptized by immersion. This option is for those who were members of a Baptist church that is no longer functioning or members of a church of another Christian denomination.<\\/p> <p>For additional information on church membership, please fill out a White Connect Card on Sunday or contact the church at <a href=\\\"mailto:info@thecreekchurch.com\\\">info@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:14:07','2015-05-13 18:14:07','042bc457-52af-4f0c-b1a8-372de57fcb19'),(32,39,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Celebrate Recovery\",\"slug\":\"celebrate-recovery\",\"postDate\":1431540876,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Do you have a hurt, habit or hang-up that is holding you back? Are you looking for real hope and meaning in your life? Would you like to find a safe, non-judgmental environment for sharing your struggles? If you answered yes to any of these questions, Celebrate Recovery is for you.<\\/p><p>No matter what the issue, Celebrate Recovery is a safe place to begin a Christ-centered recovery process. Our goal is to move toward overcoming addictive behaviors through community, scripture, and worship. As men and women share their struggles, strengths, hurts, experience and hope with each other, the Holy Spirit will lead you to begin living a life for Jesus Christ free of bondage.<\\/p><p>\\u201cWith God we will gain the victory, and He will trample down our enemies.\\u201d \\u2013 Psalm 60:12<\\/p><p><strong>What is Celebrate Recovery?<\\/strong><br> Celebrate Recovery is a 12-step, Christ-centered recovery program that helps people overcome their hurts, habits, and hang-ups. The program emphasizes \\u201c8 Recovery Principles\\u201d that are rooted in the teachings of Christ and make biblical comparisons to the 12-step program used by AA. By applying these scriptural principles to our lives, we begin growing spiritually and moving toward a life free of bondage.<\\/p><p><strong>When and where does Celebrate Recovery meet?<\\/strong><br> Celebrate Recovery meets on Tuesday nights at our new campus, located at 75 Capital Drive, in the London-Laurel County Industrial Park. Activities begin begin at 6:00 pm with a coffee and fellowship time, 6:30 pm for worship and large group, and 7:30 pm for small groups.<\\/p><p><strong>How do I learn more?<\\/strong><br> For more information please contact <a href=\\\"mailto:debbie@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">debbie@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a> \\/ 606.682.3182.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:14:36','2015-05-13 18:14:36','57582955-e794-4869-a3d4-55cea6f21e68'),(33,40,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Counseling Services\",\"slug\":\"counseling-services\",\"postDate\":1431540901,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The Pastoral Counseling Ministry exists to meet many of the relational, emotional, and spiritual needs of individual and families by providing Biblically-based, Christ-centered counseling.<\\/p><p>Our ministry team consists of professionally trained and volunteer lay-counselors, who function under the supervision of staff pastoral counselors and licensed professional counselors.<\\/p><p><strong>Days\\/Hours for Counseling<\\/strong><br> Generally speaking, appointment times are as follows:<\\/p><p>-Monday 1:00 pm \\u2013 5:00 pm<br> -Tuesday 12:00 pm \\u2013 6:00 pm<br> -Wednesday 9:00 am \\u2013 5:00 pm<br> -Thursday 9:00 am \\u2013 5:00 pm<\\/p><p>For those who cannot make these appointment times there are a limited number of evening or weekend appointments.<\\/p><p><strong>Scheduling Counseling<\\/strong><br> To schedule an appointment call 606.682.3182. We will inform you of your next step.<\\/p><p><strong>After Hour Services<\\/strong><br> We do not have an emergency call service after hours. In the case of a true, life threatening emergency, call 911 or go to your nearest hospital emergency room.<\\/p><p><strong> Privacy<\\/strong><br> We are conscious of the fact that reaching out for help is not easy. Your privacy is very important to us. All calls and appointments are treated with the greatest sensitivity and discretion.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:15:01','2015-05-13 18:15:01','0e2effae-2621-41e8-b034-6f0ba4dab8cb'),(34,41,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Community Groups\",\"slug\":\"community-groups\",\"postDate\":1431540933,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Hawk Creek can seem like a big place, but our goal is to make it feel small. Joining a Community Group is the best ways to plug in and connect. Great friendships result when you grow your faith and share life together with fun and purpose. Groups are offered for every age and stage of life.<\\/p><p>To learn more and get connected to a Community Group, contact:<br> <strong>London Campus \\u2013 Jack Willis at <strong><strong><a href=\\\"mailto:jack@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">jack@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a><\\/strong><\\/strong> or 606.224.5883<br> <\\/strong><strong>Somerset Campus \\u2013 Rocky Ryser <strong>at <a href=\\\"mailto:rocky@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">rocky@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.682.3625<\\/strong><\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>COMMUNITY GROUP Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)<\\/strong><\\/p><p><strong>What are Community Groups?<br> <\\/strong>Community Groups are made up of 8-12 adults who meet together regularly to pursue spiritual growth and healthy relationships. Groups are drawn together by common interests, stages of life, a specific topic or a particular demographic.<\\/p><p><strong>Why should I join a group?<br> <\\/strong>Groups offer a place for you to connect with others and with God, all at the same time. Groups include a variety of experiences \\u2013 relationship building, bible study, prayer and service \\u2013 all of which are intended to inspire you to become a fully devoted follower of Jesus Christ.<\\/p><p><strong>When and where do groups meet?<br> <\\/strong>Groups meet at various and times and locations on Sunday and throughout the week.<\\/p> <strong>What about Groups for my kids?<br> <\\/strong>Children experience Groups on Sunday mornings in our KidsCove and KidsCreek environments. Student Groups (Grades 6-12) meet as part of the Fusion Student experience on Wednesday nights at 6:30 pm. <p><strong>How do I find a Community Group?<\\/strong><br> To get plugged in to a Community Group, contact:<br> <strong>London Campus \\u2013 Jack Willis at <strong><strong><a href=\\\"mailto:jack@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">jack@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a><\\/strong><\\/strong> or 606.224.5883<br> <\\/strong><strong>Somerset Campus \\u2013 Rocky Ryser <strong>at <a href=\\\"mailto:rocky@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">rocky@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.682.3625<\\/strong><\\/strong><\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:15:33','2015-05-13 18:15:33','b2b36648-3f58-4ec7-a14a-da5be9ac58b7'),(35,42,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Missions\",\"slug\":\"missions\",\"postDate\":1431540979,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>International Missions<\\/strong><br> We have a passion for serving people and sharing the Gospel message both locally and globally. Our mandate to \\u201cmake disciples, of all nations\\u201d comes from Matthew 28:19-20. One way we seek to accomplish this command is through short-term mission trips that are designed to grow your relationship with Christ while serving others. We also seek to fulfill the Great Commission by supporting missionaries around the globe.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:16:19','2015-05-13 18:16:19','5a816c79-daff-45a9-9cc1-7db12ce1e6f1'),(36,43,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Love Loud\",\"slug\":\"love-loud\",\"postDate\":1431541008,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p><strong>Love Loud <\\/strong><br> Throughout the year, we conduct a variety of \\u201cLove Loud\\u201d projects that reach out into the community to shine the light of Jesus Christ. The motto of our Love Loud projects is: \\u201cActions Speak Louder Than Words.\\u201d We take our motivation straight from the Bible and believe, as followers of Christ, that we are called to serve others in real, tangible ways.<\\/p><p>Love Loud activities include shoe drives, food drives and our popular one day event where volunteers provide FREE services such as oil changes for single moms and widows, dental services, health screenings, haircuts, makeovers, legal counseling and food.<\\/p><p>Activities are planned throughout the year. To find out about upcoming Love Loud projects and offer your talents for service, contact <a href=\\\"mailto:leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a><\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:16:48','2015-05-13 18:16:48','f52771fe-c27d-452c-890e-5756c564bde1'),(37,44,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Baptism\",\"slug\":\"baptism\",\"postDate\":1431541063,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"37\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:17:43','2015-05-13 18:17:43','8413bd1b-ce43-4cf7-b022-d8f20e00c9de'),(39,46,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Community Groups\",\"slug\":\"community-groups\",\"postDate\":1431541109,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"41\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:18:29','2015-05-13 18:18:29','d2616cce-fab0-42a6-a4f8-986f3f54c25c'),(40,47,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Counseling\",\"slug\":\"counseling\",\"postDate\":1431541140,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"40\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:19:00','2015-05-13 18:19:00','b51cb535-b709-4834-b4fc-11be8a33c468'),(41,48,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Celebrate Recovery\",\"slug\":\"celebrate-recovery\",\"postDate\":1431541174,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"39\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:19:34','2015-05-13 18:19:34','31d2b1e5-b562-4685-849f-6508a1e7b8e0'),(42,49,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Love Loud\",\"slug\":\"love-loud\",\"postDate\":1431541208,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"43\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:20:08','2015-05-13 18:20:08','75b8bf0b-f38a-42af-86c5-b633f2c73daf'),(44,51,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Family Ministries\",\"slug\":\"family-ministries\",\"postDate\":1431541289,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":\"\",\"13\":\"family\"}}','2015-05-13 18:21:29','2015-05-13 18:21:29','924cb874-773e-4f05-9b2f-c506cd14bec2'),(45,52,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Children\\u2019s Ministry\",\"slug\":\"childrens-ministry\",\"postDate\":1431541318,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Through our Children\\u2019s Ministry, we have the opportunity to <em>Shape the Past of a Future Generation. <\\/em>We want kids to have a vibrant church life that is second-to-none. That\\u2019s why our kids\\u2019 activities are broken into age-based environments designed to meet the unique needs of your child.<\\/p><p><strong>KidsCove (birth \\u2013 Kindergarten)<\\/strong> uses the <em>First Look <\\/em>curriculum<em> <\\/em>to give preschoolers a first impression of their loving heavenly Father. KidsCove keeps learning simple and fun, repeating one basic truth about God all month long. By the time a child graduates KidsCove, he\\/she should believe three key things: God made me, God loves me and Jesus wants to be my friend forever.<\\/p><p><strong>KidsCreek (1<sup>st<\\/sup> \\u2013 5<sup>th<\\/sup> grade)<\\/strong> is designed to take elementary-aged children on a fun, engaging journey of biblical learning. KidsCreek uses the <em>252 Basics<\\/em> curriculum and incorporates live worship, large group teaching, drama and small groups. All components of KidsCreek teach children how to apply Biblical concepts and stories to everyday life.<\\/p><p>Our children\\u2019s activities take place during our Sunday morning services. For more information, contact Leslie Ryser at <a href=\\\"mailto:leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682.<\\/p><p><strong>What should I expect on my first visit?<br> <\\/strong>Make your way to the Kids\\u2019 area and look for our check-in stations. We will ask you to provide some information about your family that we will use to place your child in our electronic check-in system. Once you are checked-in, one of our volunteers will show you to your child\\u2019s room.<\\/p><p>You and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit. Your child will receive a name tag to wear, which includes a 4-digit number that matches the pick-up tag you receive. During check-out, you will return to your child\\u2019s room and show your pick-up tag in order for your child to be released back to you.<\\/p><p><strong>What are your safety procedures?<\\/strong><br> Security is a top priority for KidsCove and KidsCreek. All children are electronically checked-in, and foot traffic to children\\u2019s rooms is limited to ensure complete safety for all children. We also keep our child-to-volunteer ratio low in order to ensure the physical safety of each child. All volunteers working with children are required to complete a background check.<\\/p><p><strong>What if my child needs me during the worship service?<\\/strong><br> If you are needed during the worship service, the 4-digit code on your pick-up tag will appear on the screens in the auditorium. When you see your child\\u2019s code, immediately exit the auditorium and head to the KidsCove check-in desk. One of our team members will direct you to your child\\u2019s room.<\\/p><p><strong>What should I expect as a regular attendee?<\\/strong><br> Each week you will come to the kids check-in area, which opens 20 minutes before the start of each service. To check-in your child, use one of our touch screens to enter the last 7-digits of the phone number used to register your child.<\\/p><p>You and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit. Your child will receive a name tag to wear, which includes a 4-digit number that matches your pick-up tag. During check-out, you will return to your child\\u2019s room and show your pick-up tag in order for your child to be released back to you.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:21:58','2015-05-13 18:21:58','b9692e40-2338-47bc-af63-feeb945101b3'),(46,53,4,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Student Ministry (6th through 12th grade)\",\"slug\":\"student-ministry-6th-through-12th-grade\",\"postDate\":1431541352,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>We believe students are searching for something with substance, something beyond the norm. That\\u2019s why our student programs have a lively atmosphere that invites and welcomes all students to plug-in, participate, and discover what God\\u2019s truth and power can do in their lives.<\\/p><p><strong>FUSION<\\/strong> is the weekly teaching environment for 6th through 12th grade students that meets Wednesdays @ 6:30 pm. Each week, students experience a combination of live worship, interactive games, relevant teaching, and, most importantly, interaction with a small group. For more information, contact <em>ryan@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/em>.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-13 18:22:32','2015-05-13 18:22:32','02e06906-3ea3-4eac-a7a6-d0d96a13b6ad'),(47,54,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Children\'s Ministries\",\"slug\":\"childrens-ministries\",\"postDate\":1431541386,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"52\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:23:06','2015-05-13 18:23:06','218e1ba6-55f5-40b8-8a28-bec55508fd37'),(48,55,7,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Student Ministries\",\"slug\":\"student-ministries\",\"postDate\":1431541414,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"53\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-13 18:23:34','2015-05-13 18:23:34','42fb2de6-ab45-43e6-8095-bf973c5bf72e'),(49,56,7,1,'en_us',1,'