TIZED?<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>As soon as you believe.<br> <\\/strong>Acts 8:12 says: \\u201cBut when they believed Philip as he preached good news about the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.\\u201d\\r\\n<\\/p><p>This doesn\\u2019t have to be immediately but the Bible teaches that baptism should follow your decision to become a Believer. There is no reason to delay. If you wait until you are \\u201cgood\\u201d enough, you will never feel ready for baptism.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>7 \\u2013 WHAT ABOUT BEING BAPTIZED TWICE?<br> <\\/strong>The Creek Church recommends being baptized again if you have not been baptized by immersion since you became a Believer in Christ. It does not devalue a prior experience but simply reflects your desire to be baptized in the same way Jesus was baptized.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>8 \\u2013 WHAT DO I WEAR TO BE BAPTIZED?<br> <\\/strong>Dress in clothes you don\\u2019t mind getting wet. We will give you a dark shirt to wear and recommend shorts. Be sure to bring a change of dry clothes to wear home. There is a changing room available. We will provide you with a towel but recommend you also bring one from home. Arrive 30 minutes before the service is scheduled to begin for some final instructions.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>9 \\u2013 HOW DO I SIGN UP TO BE BAPTIZED?<br> <\\/strong>You can sign up to be baptized by contacting Ron Green at <a href=\\\"mailto:ron@thecreekchurch.com\\\">ron@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-15 21:47:49','2015-05-15 21:47:49','7dd4ef97-5008-4ab4-8c76-d70e95826227'),(78,37,4,1,'en_us',5,'','{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Baptism\",\"slug\":\"baptism\",\"postDate\":1431540780,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Are you a follower of Jesus Christ? If so, have you gone public with your faith? At The Creek, we teach that every person who has accepted Christ should be baptized by water immersion. <strong>If you are a follower of Christ but have never been baptized by immersion, you are invited and encouraged to do so at our next Going Public service. <\\/strong>To be included in our next Going Public Service, contact:\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>London Campus \\u2013 Ron Green at <a href=\\\"mailto:ron@thecreekchurch.com\\\">ron@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682<br> Somerset Campus \\u2013 Rocky Ryser at <a href=\\\"mailto:rocky@thecreekchurch.com\\\">rocky@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.682.3625<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p>For more information on what we teach about baptism, check out some of the Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) below. <\\/p><p><img style=\\\"width: 100%;\\\" rel=\\\"width: 100%;\\\" src=\\\"http:\\/\\/craft.dev\\/assets\\/images\\/baptism.png#asset:77:url\\\">\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>BAPTISM FAQ<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>1 \\u2013 WHY SHOULD I BE BAPTIZED?<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>To follow the example set by Christ.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cIn those days Jesus came from Nazareth of Galilee and was baptized by John in the Jordan.\\u201d (Mark 1:9)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>Because Christ commanded it.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cGo therefore and make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and of the Son and of the Holy Spirit, teaching them to observe all that I have commanded you. And behold, I am with you always, to the end of the age.\\u201d (Matthew 28:19-20)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>It demonstrates that I am a Believer.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cAnd by this we know that we have come to know him, if we keep his commandments.\\u201d (1 John 2:3)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>2 \\u2013 WHAT IS THE MEANING OF BAPTISM?<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>To illustrate Christ\\u2019s death, burial and resurrection.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cChrist died for our sins in accordance with the Scriptures, that he was buried, that he was raised on the third day in accordance with the Scriptures\\u201d (1 Corinthians 15:3-4)\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\u201cHaving been buried with him in baptism, in which you were also raised with him through faith in the powerful working of God, who raised him from the dead.\\u201d (Colossians 2:12)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>To illustrate my new life as a Christian.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cTherefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old has passed away; behold, the new has come.\\u201d (2 Corinthians 5:17)\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\u201cWe were buried therefore with him by baptism into death, in order that, just as Christ was raised from the dead by the glory of the Father, we too might walk in newness of life.\\u201d (Romans 6:4)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>3 \\u2013 IS BAPTISM NECESSARY FOR SALVATION?<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>No, baptism doesn\\u2019t make you a Christian.<br> <\\/strong>Only your faith in Christ makes you a Christian. Baptism is a public sign of the commitment you have made to follow Jesus Christ.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\u201cFor by grace you have been saved through faith. And this is not your own doing; it is the gift of God, not a result of works, so that no one may boast.\\u201d (Ephesians 2:8-9)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>4 \\u2013 WHY BE BAPTIZED BY IMMERSION?<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>Because Jesus was baptized by immersion.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cAnd when Jesus was baptized, immediately he went up from the water\\u2026\\u201d (Matthew 3:16)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>Every baptism in the Bible was by immersion.<br> <\\/strong>For example: \\u201cAnd he commanded the chariot to stop, and they both went down into the water, Philip and the eunuch, and he baptized him.\\u201d (Acts 8:38)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>The word \\u201cbaptize\\u201d comes from the Greek word \\u201cbaptizo\\u201d which means \\u201cto dip\\u201d or \\u201cto immerse\\u201d under water.<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>It best symbolizes a burial and resurrection<br> <\\/strong>As a person being baptized goes under water, he\\/she is identifying with the death of and burial of Christ. As he\\/she comes up out of the water, he\\/she is identifying with the resurrection of Christ. (see Romans 6:1-11)\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong> 5 \\u2013 WHO SHOULD BE BAPTIZED?<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>Every person who has believed in Jesus Christ.<br> <\\/strong>\\u201cSo those who received his word were baptized, and there were added that day about three thousand souls.\\u201d (Acts 2:41)\\r\\n<\\/p><p>\\u201cBut when they believed Philip as he preached good news about the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.\\u201d (Acts 8:12)<br> <strong><br> The one requirement for baptism is belief in Christ.<br> <\\/strong>A Believer is someone who has realized that their sin separated them from God. They have given up all efforts to reach God through good works or religious activity. They have concluded that Jesus Christ\\u2019s death on the cross for their sins is the only thing that can bridge the gap between them and God. A Believer is someone who has decided to trust Christ alone for their salvation. If you have come to that point in your spiritual journey, then you are ready to be baptized.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>6 \\u2013 WHEN SHOULD I BE BAPTIZED?<\\/strong>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>As soon as you believe.<br> <\\/strong>Acts 8:12 says: \\u201cBut when they believed Philip as he preached good news about the kingdom of God and the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized, both men and women.\\u201d\\r\\n<\\/p><p>This doesn\\u2019t have to be immediately but the Bible teaches that baptism should follow your decision to become a Believer. There is no reason to delay. If you wait until you are \\u201cgood\\u201d enough, you will never feel ready for baptism.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>7 \\u2013 WHAT ABOUT BEING BAPTIZED TWICE?<br> <\\/strong>The Creek Church recommends being baptized again if you have not been baptized by immersion since you became a Believer in Christ. It does not devalue a prior experience but simply reflects your desire to be baptized in the same way Jesus was baptized.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>8 \\u2013 WHAT DO I WEAR TO BE BAPTIZED?<br> <\\/strong>Dress in clothes you don\\u2019t mind getting wet. We will give you a dark shirt to wear and recommend shorts. Be sure to bring a change of dry clothes to wear home. There is a changing room available. We will provide you with a towel but recommend you also bring one from home. Arrive 30 minutes before the service is scheduled to begin for some final instructions.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>9 \\u2013 HOW DO I SIGN UP TO BE BAPTIZED?<br> <\\/strong>You can sign up to be baptized by contacting Ron Green at <a href=\\\"mailto:ron@thecreekchurch.com\\\">ron@thecreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-15 21:48:12','2015-05-15 21:48:12','584f8746-b2a3-4e96-b9a3-08c927e2ca6b'),(79,79,10,1,'en_us',1,'','{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Children\'s Ministries\",\"slug\":\"childrensministries\",\"postDate\":1432047488,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Through our Children\\u2019s Ministry, we have the opportunity to <em>Shape the Past of a Future Generation. <\\/em>We want kids to have a vibrant church life that is second-to-none. That\\u2019s why our kids\\u2019 activities are broken into age-based environments designed to meet the unique needs of your child.<\\/p><p><strong>KidsCove (birth \\u2013 Kindergarten)<\\/strong> uses the <em>First Look <\\/em>curriculum<em> <\\/em>to give preschoolers a first impression of their loving heavenly Father. KidsCove keeps learning simple and fun, repeating one basic truth about God all month long. By the time a child graduates KidsCove, he\\/she should believe three key things: God made me, God loves me and Jesus wants to be my friend forever.<\\/p><p><strong>KidsCreek (1<sup>st<\\/sup> \\u2013 5<sup>th<\\/sup> grade)<\\/strong> is designed to take elementary-aged children on a fun, engaging journey of biblical learning. KidsCreek uses the <em>252 Basics<\\/em> curriculum and incorporates live worship, large group teaching, drama and small groups. All components of KidsCreek teach children how to apply Biblical concepts and stories to everyday life.<\\/p><p>Our children\\u2019s activities take place during our Sunday morning services. For more information, contact Leslie Ryser at <a href=\\\"mailto:leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682.<\\/p><p><strong>What should I expect on my first visit?<br> <\\/strong>Make your way to the Kids\\u2019 area and look for our check-in stations. We will ask you to provide some information about your family that we will use to place your child in our electronic check-in system. Once you are checked-in, one of our volunteers will show you to your child\\u2019s room.<\\/p><p>You and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit. Your child will receive a name tag to wear, which includes a 4-digit number that matches the pick-up tag you receive. During check-out, you will return to your child\\u2019s room and show your pick-up tag in order for your child to be released back to you.<\\/p><p><strong>What are your safety procedures?<\\/strong><br> Security is a top priority for KidsCove and KidsCreek. All children are electronically checked-in, and foot traffic to children\\u2019s rooms is limited to ensure complete safety for all children. We also keep our child-to-volunteer ratio low in order to ensure the physical safety of each child. All volunteers working with children are required to complete a background check.<\\/p><p><strong>What if my child needs me during the worship service?<\\/strong><br> If you are needed during the worship service, the 4-digit code on your pick-up tag will appear on the screens in the auditorium. When you see your child\\u2019s code, immediately exit the auditorium and head to the KidsCove check-in desk. One of our team members will direct you to your child\\u2019s room.<\\/p><p><strong>What should I expect as a regular attendee?<\\/strong><br> Each week you will come to the kids check-in area, which opens 20 minutes before the start of each service. To check-in your child, use one of our touch screens to enter the last 7-digits of the phone number used to register your child.<\\/p><p>You and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit. Your child will receive a name tag to wear, which includes a 4-digit number that matches your pick-up tag. During check-out, you will return to your child\\u2019s room and show your pick-up tag in order for your child to be released back to you.<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-19 14:59:21','2015-05-19 14:59:21','b3626691-2aaa-4bcd-ad4f-d2d98d645696'),(80,54,7,1,'en_us',2,'','{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Children\'s Ministries\",\"slug\":\"childrens-ministries\",\"postDate\":1431541380,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"12\":[\"79\"],\"13\":\"\"}}','2015-05-19 16:38:20','2015-05-19 16:38:20','004afacd-3967-4965-8519-1b0b4d326606'),(81,29,4,1,'en_us',2,'','{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"What We Believe\",\"slug\":\"what-we-believe\",\"postDate\":1431540420,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Our Mission<\\/p><p>Our Vision<br><\\/p><p><strong>THE SCRIPTURES:<\\/strong> We believe that the entire Bible, all 66 books are inspired by God and inerrant in the original writings. Through the providence of God, the Word of God has been protected and preserved, and is the only infallible and authoritative rule of faith and practice. \\u2013 2 Timothy 3:16-17; 2 Peter 1:20-21; Psalm 119:11, 89, 105\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>GOD<\\/strong>: We believe there is only One true, eternally existent God. He exists in three co-equal persons \\u2013 Father, Son, and Holy Spirit. The triune God is the Creator and Sustainer of all things, and is worthy of worship and obedience. \\u2013 Deuteronomy. 6:4-5; Genesis 1:31, Luke 3:21-22; Matthew 28:18-20\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>JESUS CHRIST:<\\/strong> We believe that Jesus Christ is God. He was conceived by the Holy Spirit, born of a virgin, lived a sinless life, performed miracles, shed His blood on the cross to pay the debt for our sins, was buried, bodily resurrected, ascended to the right hand of the Father, and will return literally, visibly, and personally in glory and power. \\u2013 Matthew 1:18-23; Philippians 2:5-11; 1 Corinthians 15:1-8.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>HOLY SPIRIT:<\\/strong> We believe that the Holy Spirit is God, Co-equal and Co-existent with the Father and the Son. He is the Chief Convictor of sin and the Chief Agent of regeneration and sanctification. The Holy Spirit lives within every believer and empowers every believer to live a godly life. \\u2013 John 14:16-17; 16:7-15; 1 Corinthians 6:19-20; Romans 8:9-11.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>SALVATION:<\\/strong> We believe salvation is a free gift of God\\u2019s grace apart from human works, based solely upon Christ\\u2019s atoning death, received only through faith in the person and finished work of Jesus Christ on the cross and His resurrection from death. \\u2013 Ephesians 2:8-10; Acts 16:31.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>THE CHURCH:<\\/strong> We believe the church is the body of Christ and family of God. It is made up of saved and baptized believers, who regularly join together for worship, fellowship, and ministry. \\u2013 Matthew 16:15-19; I Corinthians 12:12-14; Hebrews 10:25.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><strong>EVANGELISM:<\\/strong> We believe that it is the responsibility and privilege of every Christian to proclaim the good news of Jesus Christ and to seek to make growing disciples. \\u2013 Matthew 28:18-20; Acts 1:8.\\r\\n<\\/p>\"}}','2015-05-19 18:25:41','2015-05-19 18:25:41','3332a19f-144d-4a10-9472-12af253aa88d'),(82,33,7,1,'en_us',2,'','{\"typeId\":\"7\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"What We Believe\",\"slug\":\"our-beliefs\",\"postDate\":1431540540,\"expiry