th grade students that meets Wednesdays @ 6:30 pm. Each week, students experience a combination of live worship, interactive games, relevant teaching, and, most importantly, interaction with a small group. For more information, contact <em>ryan@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/em>.<\\/p>\",\"24\":[\"88\"]}}','2015-05-19 19:48:16','2015-05-19 19:48:16','8ce10b2a-db64-4fb9-abfc-28c92f75a9c5'),(92,79,10,1,'en_us',2,'','{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Children\'s Ministries\",\"slug\":\"childrensministries\",\"postDate\":1432064967,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Through our Children\\u2019s Ministry, we have the opportunity to <em>Shape the Past of a Future Generation. <\\/em>We want kids to have a vibrant church life that is second-to-none. That\\u2019s why our kids\\u2019 activities are broken into age-based environments designed to meet the unique needs of your child.<\\/p><p><strong>KidsCove (birth \\u2013 Kindergarten)<\\/strong> uses the <em>First Look <\\/em>curriculum<em> <\\/em>to give preschoolers a first impression of their loving heavenly Father. KidsCove keeps learning simple and fun, repeating one basic truth about God all month long. By the time a child graduates KidsCove, he\\/she should believe three key things: God made me, God loves me and Jesus wants to be my friend forever.<\\/p><p><strong>KidsCreek (1<sup>st<\\/sup> \\u2013 5<sup>th<\\/sup> grade)<\\/strong> is designed to take elementary-aged children on a fun, engaging journey of biblical learning. KidsCreek uses the <em>252 Basics<\\/em> curriculum and incorporates live worship, large group teaching, drama and small groups. All components of KidsCreek teach children how to apply Biblical concepts and stories to everyday life.<\\/p><p>Our children\\u2019s activities take place during our Sunday morning services. For more information, contact Leslie Ryser at <a href=\\\"mailto:leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682.<\\/p><p><strong>What should I expect on my first visit?<br> <\\/strong>Make your way to the Kids\\u2019 area and look for our check-in stations. We will ask you to provide some information about your family that we will use to place your child in our electronic check-in system. Once you are checked-in, one of our volunteers will show you to your child\\u2019s room.<\\/p><p>You and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit. Your child will receive a name tag to wear, which includes a 4-digit number that matches the pick-up tag you receive. During check-out, you will return to your child\\u2019s room and show your pick-up tag in order for your child to be released back to you.<\\/p><p><strong>What are your safety procedures?<\\/strong><br> Security is a top priority for KidsCove and KidsCreek. All children are electronically checked-in, and foot traffic to children\\u2019s rooms is limited to ensure complete safety for all children. We also keep our child-to-volunteer ratio low in order to ensure the physical safety of each child. All volunteers working with children are required to complete a background check.<\\/p><p><strong>What if my child needs me during the worship service?<\\/strong><br> If you are needed during the worship service, the 4-digit code on your pick-up tag will appear on the screens in the auditorium. When you see your child\\u2019s code, immediately exit the auditorium and head to the KidsCove check-in desk. One of our team members will direct you to your child\\u2019s room.<\\/p><p><strong>What should I expect as a regular attendee?<\\/strong><br> Each week you will come to the kids check-in area, which opens 20 minutes before the start of each service. To check-in your child, use one of our touch screens to enter the last 7-digits of the phone number used to register your child.<\\/p><p>You and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit. Your child will receive a name tag to wear, which includes a 4-digit number that matches your pick-up tag. During check-out, you will return to your child\\u2019s room and show your pick-up tag in order for your child to be released back to you.<\\/p>\",\"24\":[\"80\"]}}','2015-05-19 19:50:07','2015-05-19 19:50:07','e6028563-3ee1-4e72-8b0b-ce34f0cc6fc6'),(93,79,10,1,'en_us',3,'','{\"typeId\":\"10\",\"authorId\":null,\"title\":\"Children\'s Ministries\",\"slug\":\"childrensministries\",\"postDate\":1432064967,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Through our Children\\u2019s Ministry, we have the opportunity to <em>Shape the Past of a Future Generation. <\\/em>We want kids to have a vibrant church life that is second-to-none. That\\u2019s why our kids\\u2019 activities are broken into age-based environments designed to meet the unique needs of your child.<\\/p><p><strong>KidsCove (birth \\u2013 Kindergarten)<\\/strong> uses the <em>First Look <\\/em>curriculum<em> <\\/em>to give preschoolers a first impression of their loving heavenly Father. KidsCove keeps learning simple and fun, repeating one basic truth about God all month long. By the time a child graduates KidsCove, he\\/she should believe three key things: God made me, God loves me and Jesus wants to be my friend forever.<\\/p><p><strong>KidsCreek (1<sup>st<\\/sup> \\u2013 5<sup>th<\\/sup> grade)<\\/strong> is designed to take elementary-aged children on a fun, engaging journey of biblical learning. KidsCreek uses the <em>252 Basics<\\/em> curriculum and incorporates live worship, large group teaching, drama and small groups. All components of KidsCreek teach children how to apply Biblical concepts and stories to everyday life.<\\/p><p>Our children\\u2019s activities take place during our Sunday morning services. For more information, contact Leslie Ryser at <a href=\\\"mailto:leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com\\\">leslie@hawkcreekchurch.com<\\/a> or 606.877.9682.<\\/p><p><strong>What should I expect on