INSERT INTO `craft_searchindex` VALUES (1,'username',0,'en_us',' joshshane '),(1,'firstname',0,'en_us',''),(1,'lastname',0,'en_us',''),(1,'fullname',0,'en_us',''),(1,'email',0,'en_us',' joshshane gmail com '),(1,'slug',0,'en_us',''),(2,'field',1,'en_us',' it s true this site doesn t have a whole lot of content yet but don t worry our web developers have just installed the cms and they re setting things up for the content editors this very moment soon craft dev will be an oasis of fresh perspectives sharp analyses and astute opinions that will keep you coming back again and again '),(2,'slug',0,'en_us',' homepage '),(2,'title',0,'en_us',' homepage '),(23,'slug',0,'en_us',' about us '),(23,'title',0,'en_us',' about us '),(24,'field',1,'en_us',' our staff is awesome they are the best '),(24,'slug',0,'en_us',' staff page '),(24,'title',0,'en_us',' staff page '),(25,'field',12,'en_us',' our staff '),(25,'field',13,'en_us',''),(25,'slug',0,'en_us',' staff '),(25,'title',0,'en_us',' staff '),(23,'field',13,'en_us',' about '),(23,'field',12,'en_us',''),(7,'kind',0,'en_us',' image '),(7,'extension',0,'en_us',' jpg '),(7,'filename',0,'en_us',' flir0015 jpg '),(5,'filename',0,'en_us',' drivesession2 mp3 '),(5,'extension',0,'en_us',' mp3 '),(5,'kind',0,'en_us',' audio '),(5,'slug',0,'en_us',' drivesession2 '),(5,'title',0,'en_us',' drivesession2 '),(6,'filename',0,'en_us',' penguins jpg '),(6,'extension',0,'en_us',' jpg '),(6,'kind',0,'en_us',' image '),(6,'slug',0,'en_us',' penguins '),(6,'title',0,'en_us',' penguins '),(7,'slug',0,'en_us',' flir0015 '),(7,'title',0,'en_us',' flir0015 '),(11,'field',1,'en_us',' welcome to hawk creek church it is our hope that you discover a warm friendly group of people at the creek whether you re single married with or without children no matter where you ve been or what you ve done you are welcome here this section of our website will help you find out more about our story beliefs vision and staff next steps will help you discover how to move forward in your relationship with god children and student ministries provide information on how we are reaching the next generation be sure to check out our messages at our watch listen section relax and enjoy your visit we are glad you are here '),(9,'field',5,'en_us',''),(9,'slug',0,'en_us',''),(9,'field',4,'en_us',''),(11,'slug',0,'en_us',' about '),(11,'title',0,'en_us',' new here '),(12,'field',7,'en_us',' lead pastor '),(12,'field',8,'en_us',' trevor thecreekchurch com '),(12,'field',9,'en_us',' trevor is the lead pastor of the creek church a native of middlesboro kentucky trevor came to the creek in november of 2004 under his leadership the church has grown from a small community fellowship into a thriving outwardly focused instrument of change trevor is a gifted communicator and teacher with a passion for presenting biblical truth in a dynamic relevant way his passion is to lead people from all walks of life into an authentic growing relationship with jesus christ trevor and his wife allison have two sons shepherd and greyson '),(12,'slug',0,'en_us',' trevor barton '),(12,'title',0,'en_us',' trevor barton '),(13,'field',7,'en_us',' guest services director '),(13,'field',8,'en_us',' donna thecreekchurch com '),(13,'field',9,'en_us',' as guest services director donna helps mobilize a team of weekly volunteers that seek to make first time guests and regular attendees feel welcome from the moment they drive into the parking lot until after they head home '),(13,'slug',0,'en_us',' donna mcclure '),(13,'title',0,'en_us',' donna mcclure '),(14,'field',7,'en_us',' director of celebrate recovery pastoral counseling '),(14,'field',8,'en_us',' debbie thecreekchurch com '),(14,'field',9,'en_us',' debbie came to hawk creek in march of 2006 later that year she began fasting and praying asking god to break her heart for what breaks his she sensed god calling her into marriage and family ministries and has been passionately pursuing that challenge ever since debbie holds a bachelor s degree in education from berea college and a master s degree in marriage and family therapy from liberty university she counsels from a biblical worldview and believes god is the healer of marriages and families she and her husband doug have one adult son named kris '),(14,'slug',0,'en_us',' debbie gilbert '),(14,'title',0,'en_us',' debbie gilbert '),(15,'field',7,'en_us',' director of children s ministries love loud '),(15,'field',8,'en_us',' leslie thecreekchurch com '),(15,'field',9,'en_us',' leslie has a passion for helping children and families become fully devoted followers of christ before coming to the creek leslie worked in washington dc where she was part of a dynamic church body she learned that biblical community doesn t have to be boring it should be exciting relevant and fun she s been sold out on serving jesus ever since as kids director leslie leads our kidscove and kidscreek environments she also heads up our love loud projects leslie and her husband rocky have a son named ross '),(15,'slug',0,'en_us',' leslie ryser '),(15,'title',0,'en_us',' leslie ryser '),(16,'field',7,'en_us',' student pastor '),(16,'field',8,'en_us',' ryan thecreekchurch com '),(16,'field',9,'en_us',' ryan is the student pastor here at hawk creek he has a passion for leading students to become fully devoted followers of jesus christ a native of london ryan has been actively involved at the creek since 2006 and has served in a variety of areas including our worship somerset campus and media ministries ryan holds a bachelor s degree in bible from tennessee temple university he is an avid runner reader and thinker '),(16,'slug',0,'en_us',' ryan hartzell '),(16,'title',0,'en_us',' ryan hartzell '),(17,'field',7,'en_us',' worship leader '),(17,'field',8,'en_us',''),(17,'field',9,'en_us',' shane has been involved with christian music for more than a decade and serves as one of our worship leaders he is an avid fan of all types of music and has a passion for using worship to draw people into a closer relationship with christ shane and his wife jessica are involved with our fusion student ministry they are the proud parents of two children haley and dylan in addition to serving at the creek shane works as a network engineer for the laurel county school system '),(17,'slug',0,'en_us',' shane mccowan '),(17,'title',0,'en_us',' shane mccowan '),(18,'field',7,'en_us',' creative arts pastor '),(18,'field',8,'en_us',' austin thecreekchurch com '),(18,'field',9,'en_us',' as creative arts pastor austin leads the creative arts team to produce and deliver content that leads people to take a step closer to jesus austin is passionate about developing visual media that provokes thought and ultimately action he is driven and inspired by colossians 3 23 i will pursue excellence in everything i do because i m working for god not man austin is an avid fisherman and enjoys playing guitar he and his wife jessie enjoy watching movies shopping traveling and cooking together '),(18,'slug',0,'en_us',' austin upchurch '),(18,'title',0,'en_us',' austin upchurch '),(19,'field',7,'en_us',''),(19,'field',8,'en_us',' jonathan thecreekchurch com '),(19,'field',9,'en_us',' as finance pastor jonathan has oversight of the financials and accounting he also serves as the production director where he leads the production team for sunday services and special events jonathan graduated from cumberland college in 2004 with a double major earning bachelor of science degrees in business administration and computer information systems jonathan and his wife erica have three daughters including a set of identical twins '),(19,'slug',0,'en_us',' jonathan bright '),(19,'title',0,'en_us',' jonathan bright '),(20,'field',7,'en_us',' next steps administrator '),(20,'field',8,'en_us',' jack thecreekchurch com '),(20,'field',9,'en_us',' jack serves as our next steps pastor and administrator guiding our new attendees to find their place at the creek as well as overseeing day to day operations a native of corbin kentucky jack graduated from cumberland college in 2001 with a bachelor of science degree minor in special education jack is happily married to his wife suzanne they have a son named jackson and a daughter named karis '),(20,'slug',0,'en_us',' jack willis '),(20,'title',0,'en_us',' jack willis '),(21,'field',10,'en_us',' http www bbcnews com '),(21,'slug',0,'en_us',' cvas '),(21,'title',0,'en_us',' cva form '),(22,'field',10,'en_us',' http www cnn com '),(22,'slug',0,'en_us',' cvas '),(22,'title',0,'en_us',' last year s cva '),(26,'field',1,'en_us',' first don t stress over what to wear we try to project a casual environment on any typical sunday our pastor and worship teams will lead the way by sporting jeans and such feel free to dress comfortably and casually from the moment you arrive on our campus you will find a friendly helpful atmosphere parking teams will assist you to our reserved parking area which exists for guests seniors and those with special needs once inside feel free to grab a cup of coffee or a light breakfast in our creek cafe also our guest services center will be staffed by smiling volunteers ready and eager to answer any questions you might have there you will also find various resources available for purchase that can help you in your journey of faith in addition to books by leading authors cds and dvds of our worship experiences are available the doors to the auditorium as well as the doors to kidscreek and kidscove open 15 minutes before our 9 30 am and 11 15 am services prior to the auditorium doors opening you will find ample space and lots of seating available in the cafe and foyer areas come early hang out with your family or friends and meet other creekers we have a first class facility ready to serve your children from birth through 5th grade our nursery is fully staffed by people who love kids our pre school and children s worship experience are also fully staffed by adults who want to love and lead your children to an incredible experience every single sunday our worship experience is typically 70 minutes of dynamic relevant high energy music coupled with practical yet theological teaching we believe that the church is never supposed to be boring or predictable our goal is to provide a world class worship experience every sunday in order that jesus may be made famous in our community and world at the conclusion of each worship experience you will be invited to a pastor s reception area where you can meet our lead pastor and receive a special gift from the creek just for being with us we hope your experience at the creek will be all you expected '),(26,'slug',0,'en_us',' what to expect '),(26,'title',0,'en_us',' what to expect '),(27,'field',1,'en_us',' the creek church was founded in 1861 as hawk creek baptist church for 144 years the church existed as a small community church predominantly serving those living in and near the hawk creek area of laurel county kentucky in the early days the average attendance ranged from 50 to 100 people in 2005 god began a fresh move that brought revival and expanded the churches borders to reach throughout laurel county the region and into the world today god is radically transforming and rebuilding lives at hawk creek since 2005 over 1000 people have been baptized and come to develop a personal relationship with jesus christ through the dynamic presentation of god s unchanging word and the hands of his people addictions have been shattered broken marriages have been rebuilt and lives have been reborn in february 2011 we moved into a new state of the art building located on a 40 acre campus in the london laurel county industrial park the facility strategically positions us to make a bigger difference in our community and the world for generations to come in march 2012 we launched a second campus in somerset kentucky we are now one church meeting in two locations our mission remains the same to love god and love people and to lead those people to become fully devoted followers of jesus christ our vision for the future compels us to believe that the best days are still ahead '),(27,'slug',0,'en_us',' our story '),(27,'title',0,'en_us',' our story '),(29,'field',1,'en_us',' our mission to love god and love people and to lead those people to become fully devoted followers of jesus christ our vision to create a church that people who don t like church love to attend the scriptures we believe that the entire bible all 66 books are inspired by god and inerrant in the original writings through the providence of god the word of god has been protected and preserved and is the only infallible and authoritative rule of faith and practice 2 timothy 3 16 17 2 peter 1 20 21 psalm 119 11 89 105 god we believe there is only one true eternally existent god he exists in three co equal persons father son and holy spirit the triune god is the creator and sustainer of all things and is worthy of worship and obedience deuteronomy 6 4 5 genesis 1 31 luke 3 21 22 matthew 28 18 20 jesus christ we believe that jesus christ is god he was conceived by the holy spirit born of a virgin lived a sinless life performed miracles shed his blood on the cross to pay the debt for our sins was buried bodily resurrected ascended to the right hand of the father and will return literally visibly and personally in glory and power matthew 1 18 23 philippians 2 5 11 1 corinthians 15 1 8 holy spirit we believe that the holy spirit is god co equal and co existent with the father and the son he is the chief convictor of sin and the chief agent of regeneration and sanctification the holy spirit lives within every believer and empowers every believer to live a godly life john 14 16 17 16 7 15 1 corinthians 6 19 20 romans 8 9 11 salvation we believe salvation is a free gift of god s grace apart from human works based solely upon christ s atoning death received only through faith in the person and finished work of jesus christ on the cross and his resurrection from death ephesians 2 8 10 acts 16 31 the church we believe the church is the body of christ and family of god it is made up of saved and baptized believers who regularly join together for worship fellowship and ministry matthew 16 15 19 i corinthians 12 12 14 hebrews 10 25 evangelism we believe that it is the responsibility and privilege of every christian to proclaim the good news of jesus christ and to seek to make growing disciples matthew 28 18 20 acts 1 8 '),(29,'slug',0,'en_us',' what we believe '),(29,'title',0,'en_us',' what we believe '),(30,'field',12,'en_us',' what to expect '),(30,'field',13,'en_us',''),(30,'slug',0,'en_us',' what to expect '),(30,'title',0,'en_us',' what to expect '),(31,'field',12,'en_us',' our story '),(31,'field',13,'en_us',''),(31,'slug',0,'en_us',' our story '),(31,'title',0,'en_us',' our story '),(33,'field',12,'en_us',' what we believe '),(33,'field',13,'en_us',''),(33,'slug',0,'en_us',' our beliefs '),(33,'title',0,'en_us',' what we believe '),(34,'field',1,'en_us',' london weekly activities weekend services sunday 9 30am 11 15am the creek kids sunday 9 30am 11 15am fusion students wednesday 6 30 pm celebrate recovery tuesday 6 00 pm location the creek church 75 capital drive london ky 40741 off industrial blvd hwy 80 west see map directions somerset weekly activities weekend services sunday 10 00 am the creek kids sunday 10 00 am fusion students wednesday 6 30 pm location the center for rural development 2292 south highway 27 somerset ky 42501 see map directions church office delivery address the creek church 504 north broad street london ky 40741 phone 606 877 9682 email info thecreekchurch com '),(34,'slug',0,'en_us',' services locations '),(34,'title',0,'en_us',' services locations '),(35,'field',12,'en_us',' services locations '),(35,'field',13,'en_us',''),(35,'slug',0,'en_us',' services locations '),(35,'title',0,'en_us',' services locations '),(36,'field',12,'en_us',''),(36,'field',13,'en_us',''),(36,'slug',0,'en_us',' next steps '),(36,'title',0,'en_us',' next steps '),(37,'field',1,'en_us',' are you a follower of jesus christ if so have you gone public with your faith at the creek we teach that every person who has accepted christ should be baptized by water immersion if you are a follower of christ but have never been baptized by immersion you are invited and encouraged to do so at our next going public service to be included in our next going public service contact london campus ron green at ron thecreekchurch com or 606 877 9682 somerset campus rocky ryser at rocky thecreekchurch com or 606 682 3625 for more information on what we teach about baptism check out some of the frequently asked questions faqs below baptism faq 1 why should i be baptized to follow the example set by christ in those days jesus came from nazareth of galilee and was baptized by john in the jordan mark 1 9 because christ commanded it go therefore and make disciples of all nations baptizing them in the name of the father and of the son and of the holy spirit teaching them to observe all that i have commanded you and behold i am with you always to the end of the age matthew 28 19 20 it demonstrates that i am a believer and by this we know that we have come to know him if we keep his commandments 1 john 2 3 2 what is the meaning of baptism to illustrate christ s death burial and resurrection christ died for our sins in accordance with the scriptures that he was buried that he was raised on the third day in accordance with the scriptures 1 corinthians 15 3 4 having been buried with him in baptism in which you were also raised with him through faith in the powerful working of god who raised him from the dead colossians 2 12 to illustrate my new life as a christian therefore if anyone is in christ he is a new creation the old has passed away behold the new has come 2 corinthians 5 17 we were buried therefore with him by baptism into death in order that just as christ was raised from the dead by the glory of the father we too might walk in newness of life romans 6 4 3 is baptism necessary for salvation no baptism doesn t make you a christian only your faith in christ makes you a christian baptism is a public sign of the commitment you have made to follow jesus christ for by grace you have been saved through faith and this is not your own doing it is the gift of god not a result of works so that no one may boast ephesians 2 8 9 4 why be baptized by immersion because jesus was baptized by immersion and when jesus was baptized immediately he went up from the water matthew 3 16 every baptism in the bible was by immersion for example and he commanded the chariot to stop and they both went down into the water philip and the eunuch and he baptized him acts 8 38 the word baptize comes from the greek word baptizo which means to dip or to immerse under water it best symbolizes a burial and resurrection as a person being baptized goes under water he she is identifying with the death of and burial of christ as he she comes up out of the water he she is identifying with the resurrection of christ see romans 6 1 11 5 who should be baptized every person who has believed in jesus christ so those who received his word were baptized and there were added that day about three thousand souls acts 2 41 but when they believed philip as he preached good news about the kingdom of god and the name of jesus christ they were baptized both men and women acts 8 12 the one requirement for baptism is belief in christ a believer is someone who has realized that their sin separated them from god they have given up all efforts to reach god through good works or religious activity they have concluded that jesus christ s death on the cross for their sins is the only thing that can bridge the gap between them and god a believer is someone who has decided to trust christ alone for their salvation if you have come to that point in your spiritual journey then you are ready to be baptized 6 when should i be baptized as soon as you believe acts 8 12 says but when they believed philip as he preached good news about the kingdom of god and the name of jesus christ they were baptized both men and women this doesn t have to be immediately but the bible teaches that baptism should follow your decision to become a believer there is no reason to delay if you wait until you are good enough you will never feel ready for baptism 7 what about being baptized twice the creek church recommends being baptized again if you have not been baptized by immersion since you became a believer in christ it does not devalue a prior experience but simply reflects your desire to be baptized in the same way jesus was baptized 8 what do i wear to be baptized dress in clothes you don t mind getting wet we will give you a dark shirt to wear and recommend shorts be sure to bring a change of dry clothes to wear home there is a changing room available we will provide you with a towel but recommend you also bring one from home arrive 30 minutes before the service is scheduled to begin for some final instructions 9 how do i sign up to be baptized you can sign up to be baptized by contacting ron green at ron thecreekchurch com or 606 877 9682 '),(37,'slug',0,'en_us',' baptism '),(37,'title',0,'en_us',' baptism '),(38,'field',1,'en_us',' there are three ways to become a member of the creek church baptism this means you have received jesus christ as your savior and are ready to identify with him publicly by being baptized by immersion in water transfer of a letter of membership this means you have received jesus christ as your savior been baptized by immersion and are a member of another baptist church statement of faith this means you have received jesus christ as your savior and been baptized by immersion this option is for those who were members of a baptist church that is no longer functioning or members of a church of another christian denomination for additional information on church membership please fill out a white connect card on sunday or contact the church at info thecreekchurch com or 606 877 9682 '),(38,'slug',0,'en_us',' membership '),(38,'title',0,'en_us',' membership '),(39,'field',1,'en_us',' do you have a hurt habit or hang up that is holding you back are you looking for real hope and meaning in your life would you like to find a safe non judgmental environment for sharing your struggles if you answered yes to any of these questions celebrate recovery is for you no matter what the issue celebrate recovery is a safe place to begin a christ centered recovery process our goal is to move toward overcoming addictive behaviors through community scripture and worship as men and women share their struggles strengths hurts experience and hope with each other the holy spirit will lead you to begin living a life for jesus christ free of bondage with god we will gain the victory and he will trample down our enemies psalm 60 12what is celebrate recovery celebrate recovery is a 12 step christ centered recovery program that helps people overcome their hurts habits and hang ups the program emphasizes 8 recovery principles that are rooted in the teachings of christ and make biblical comparisons to the 12 step program used by aa by applying these scriptural principles to our lives we begin growing spiritually and moving toward a life free of bondage when and where does celebrate recovery meet celebrate recovery meets on tuesday nights at our new campus located at 75 capital drive in the london laurel county industrial park activities begin begin at 6 00 pm with a coffee and fellowship time 6 30 pm for worship and large group and 7 30 pm for small groups how do i learn more for more information please contact debbie hawkcreekchurch com 606 682 3182 '),(39,'slug',0,'en_us',' celebrate recovery '),(39,'title',0,'en_us',' celebrate recovery '),(40,'field',1,'en_us',' the pastoral counseling ministry exists to meet many of the relational emotional and spiritual needs of individual and families by providing biblically based christ centered counseling our ministry team consists of professionally trained and volunteer lay counselors who function under the supervision of staff pastoral counselors and licensed professional counselors days hours for counseling generally speaking appointment times are as follows monday 1 00 pm 5 00 pm tuesday 12 00 pm 6 00 pm wednesday 9 00 am 5 00 pm thursday 9 00 am 5 00 pmfor those who cannot make these appointment times there are a limited number of evening or weekend appointments scheduling counseling to schedule an appointment call 606 682 3182 we will inform you of your next step after hour services we do not have an emergency call service after hours in the case of a true life threatening emergency call 911 or go to your nearest hospital emergency room privacy we are conscious of the fact that reaching out for help is not easy your privacy is very important to us all calls and appointments are treated with the greatest sensitivity and discretion '),(40,'slug',0,'en_us',' counseling services '),(40,'title',0,'en_us',' counseling services '),(41,'field',1,'en_us',' hawk creek can seem like a big place but our goal is to make it feel small joining a community group is the best ways to plug in and connect great friendships result when you grow your faith and share life together with fun and purpose groups are offered for every age and stage of life to learn more and get connected to a community group contact london campus jack willis at jack hawkcreekchurch com or 606 224 5883 somerset campus rocky ryser at rocky hawkcreekchurch com or 606 682 3625community group frequently asked questions faq what are community groups community groups are made up of 8 12 adults who meet together regularly to pursue spiritual growth and healthy relationships groups are drawn together by common interests stages of life a specific topic or a particular demographic why should i join a group groups offer a place for you to connect with others and with god all at the same time groups include a variety of experiences relationship building bible study prayer and service all of which are intended to inspire you to become a fully devoted follower of jesus christ when and where do groups meet groups meet at various and times and locations on sunday and throughout the week what about groups for my kids children experience groups on sunday mornings in our kidscove and kidscreek environments student groups grades 6 12 meet as part of the fusion student experience on wednesday nights at 6 30 pm how do i find a community group to get plugged in to a community group contact london campus jack willis at jack hawkcreekchurch com or 606 224 5883 somerset campus rocky ryser at rocky hawkcreekchurch com or 606 682 3625 '),(41,'slug',0,'en_us',' community groups '),(41,'title',0,'en_us',' community groups '),(42,'field',1,'en_us',' international missions we have a passion for serving people and sharing the gospel message both locally and globally our mandate to make disciples of all nations comes from matthew 28 19 20 one way we seek to accomplish this command is through short term mission trips that are designed to grow your relationship with christ while serving others we also seek to fulfill the great commission by supporting missionaries around the globe '),(42,'slug',0,'en_us',' missions '),(42,'title',0,'en_us',' missions '),(43,'field',1,'en_us',' love loud throughout the year we conduct a variety of love loud projects that reach out into the community to shine the light of jesus christ the motto of our love loud projects is actions speak louder than words we take our motivation straight from the bible and believe as followers of christ that we are called to serve others in real tangible ways love loud activities include shoe drives food drives and our popular one day event where volunteers provide free services such as oil changes for single moms and widows dental services health sc