eration we want kids to have a vibrant church life that is second to none that s why our kids activities are broken into age based environments designed to meet the unique needs of your child kidscove birth kindergarten uses the first look curriculum to give preschoolers a first impression of their loving heavenly father kidscove keeps learning simple and fun repeating one basic truth about god all month long by the time a child graduates kidscove he she should believe three key things god made me god loves me and jesus wants to be my friend forever kidscreek 1st 5th grade is designed to take elementary aged children on a fun engaging journey of biblical learning kidscreek uses the 252 basics curriculum and incorporates live worship large group teaching drama and small groups all components of kidscreek teach children how to apply biblical concepts and stories to everyday life our children s activities take place during our sunday morning services for more information contact leslie ryser at leslie hawkcreekchurch com or 606 877 9682 what should i expect on my first visit make your way to the kids area and look for our check in stations we will ask you to provide some information about your family that we will use to place your child in our electronic check in system once you are checked in one of our volunteers will show you to your child s room you and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit your child will receive a name tag to wear which includes a 4 digit number that matches the pick up tag you receive during check out you will return to your child s room and show your pick up tag in order for your child to be released back to you what are your safety procedures security is a top priority for kidscove and kidscreek all children are electronically checked in and foot traffic to children s rooms is limited to ensure complete safety for all children we also keep our child to volunteer ratio low in order to ensure the physical safety of each child all volunteers working with children are required to complete a background check what if my child needs me during the worship service if you are needed during the worship service the 4 digit code on your pick up tag will appear on the screens in the auditorium when you see your child s code immediately exit the auditorium and head to the kidscove check in desk one of our team members will direct you to your child s room what should i expect as a regular attendee each week you will come to the kids check in area which opens 20 minutes before the start of each service to check in your child use one of our touch screens to enter the last 7 digits of the phone number used to register your child you and your child will receive matching identification tags that are unique to your family and your visit your child will receive a name tag to wear which includes a 4 digit number that matches your pick up tag during check out you will return to your child s room and show your pick up tag in order for your child to be released back to you '),(52,'slug',0,'en_us',' childrens ministry '),(52,'title',0,'en_us',' children s ministry '),(53,'field',1,'en_us',' we believe students are searching for something with substance something beyond the norm that s why our student programs have a lively atmosphere that invites and welcomes all students to plug in participate and discover what god s truth and power can do in their lives fusion is the weekly teaching environment for 6th through 12th grade students that meets wednesdays 6 30 pm each week students experience a combination of live worship interactive games relevant teaching and most importantly interaction with a small group for more information contact ryan hawkcreekchurch com '),(53,'slug',0,'en_us',' student ministry 6th through 12th grade '),(53,'title',0,'en_us',' student ministry 6th through 12th grade '),(54,'field',12,'en_us',' children s ministries '),(54,'field',13,'en_us',''),(54